The paper discusses the development of a domain-specific mashup tool for research impact evaluation, which involves analyzing scientific publications through citation and content analysis. This suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), and Databases (cs.DB). However, since the focus is on the development of a tool for end-user evaluation, cs.HC is the most likely category, followed by cs.DL and cs.IR.
